dir_name = os.getcwd()
def show_images(images, title):
    num_showed_imgs_x = 10
    num_showed_imgs_y = 10

    figsize = (10, 10)
    fig, axes = plot.subplots(num_showed_imgs_y, num_showed_imgs_x, figsize = figsize)
    fig.suptitle(title)
    plot.setp(plot.gcf().get_axes(), xticks = [], yticks = [])
    for i, ax in enumerate(axes.flat):
        img = images[i][0].numpy().transpose(1, 2, 0).squeeze(axis = 2)
        ax.imshow(img, cmap = 'gray')


train_dataset = torchvision.datasets.MNIST(
    root = dir_name, train = True, download = True,
    transform = torchvision.transforms.ToTensor()
)
test_dataset = torchvision.datasets.MNIST(
    root = dir_name, train = False, download = True,
    transform = torchvision.transforms.ToTensor()
)

print('Number of train samples: {}'.format(len(train_dataset)))
show_images(train_dataset, 'Train samples')

print('Number of test samples: {}'.format(len(test_dataset)))
show_images(test_dataset, 'Test samples')

def ReLU(x):
    return np.maximum(x, 0)
def softmax(x):
    return torch.softmax(x, 1)
   # return (np.exp(x)/(np.sum(np.exp(x))))
def cross_entropy(y, u):
    return (np.sum(-1*y* np.log(u)))/y.shape
def der_ReLu(x):
     return x > 0
In [30]:
class Net(torch.nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, hw, hidden_layers, classes, learning_rate, batch_size):
        super(Net, self).__init__()
        self.hw = hw
        self.learning_rate = learning_rate
        self.batch_size = batch_size
        self.hidden_layers=hidden_layers
        self.classes = classes
        self.w1 = torch.distributions.normal.Normal(0, math.sqrt(1 / (hw))).sample((self.hw, self.hidden_layers))
        self.w2 = torch.distributions.normal.Normal(0, math.sqrt(1 / (hidden_layers))).sample((self.hidden_layers, self.classes))
        self.b1 = torch.zeros((1, self.hidden_layers))
        self.b2 = torch.zeros((1, self.hidden_layers))

    def forward(self, x)->torch.Tensor:
        self.f = torch.matmul(x, self.w1) + self.b1
        self.v = ReLU(self.f)
        self.g = torch.matmul(self.v, self.w2)
        self.u = softmax(self.g)
        return self.u

    def backward(self, x,y)->None:
        dE2 = -(y - self.u)/self.batch_size
        dE1 = torch.mul(torch.matmul(dE2, self.w2.transpose(0, 1)), der_ReLu(self.f))
        dw1 = torch.matmul(x.transpose(0, 1), dE1)
        dw2 = torch.matmul(self.v.transpose(0, 1), dE2)
        db1 = dE1.sum()
        db2 = dE2.sum()
        self.w1-=self.learning_rate*dw1
        self.w2-=self.learning_rate*dw2
        self.b1-=self.learning_rate*db1
        self.b2-=self.learning_rate*db2

def get_accuracy(data_loader, model):
    tp = 0
    n = 0
    with torch.no_grad():
        for images, labels in data_loader:
            images = images.reshape(-1, wh)
            outputs = model(images)

            _, predicted = torch.max(outputs.data, 1)
            n += labels.size(dim=0)
            tp += (predicted == labels).sum()
    return tp / n

def new_labels(labels, shape):
    new_labels = torch.zeros(shape)
    for i in range(shape[0]):
        new_labels[i, labels[i]] = 1
    return new_labels
In [37]:
def train(Network):
    for epoch in range(epochs):
        t0 = time.time()
        for images, labels in train_data_loader:
            images = images.view(-1, wh).to(device)
            labels = labels.to(device)
            y = Network.forward(images)
            new_lab = new_labels(labels, y.shape)
            Network.backward(images, new_lab)
        t1 = time.time()
        print(f'Epoch[{epoch + 1}]: accuracy = {get_accuracy(train_data_loader, Network)}, time = {t1 - t0}')
    print('Test accuracy: {}'.format(get_accuracy(test_data_loader, Network)))
